Use either of these two commands, GREP is easier to look inside of a file for a string you provide.

grep -rnw '/PATH' -e "STRING"

Example:
grep -rnw '/etc/httpd/' -e "digitas.com"
grep -rnw '/etc/httpd/' -e "monitorix"
grep -rnw '/etc/httpd/' -e "evolvragency"

Search using "find"
find ./ -type f -exec grep search_term -il {} \;
